# .docscheck-exempt — env vars whose `Used by` cell in the docs/scripts.md table
# names no script, checked by scripts/check-docs.sh.
#
# An unexempted prose cell FAILS. That is the point: it stops prose from
# silently creeping back into a machine-checked column. Every entry here is a
# deliberate, reasoned hole in the strict-consumer axis.
#
# Before adding an entry, ask the question the deny-list rounds taught: a fix
# that narrows a matcher to kill a false positive is the likeliest place to
# create a false negative. What does this line now fail to catch?
#
# Format:  VAR  # reason
# These vars are still checked by the FORWARD axis (they must exist in code).

MEMORY_DIR                 # "All scripts" — no single consumer to name; every script resolves the tree through it.
MEMORY_TASK_PROVIDER       # Read by the Python task-provider factory, not a shell script. Only a comment mentions it in _lib.sh:8.
NOTION_TOKEN               # Consumed by the NotionProvider class (scripts/taskprovider/providers/notion.py), not a named script.
NOTION_DATA_SOURCE_ID      # As above — a class, not a file.
NOTION_STATUS_KIND         # As above — a class, not a file.
